I'm creating dynamic controls on a View based on some JSON.

The JSON contains an array of controls with properties: name, value, type.

I'm retrieving these and adding them to a collection.

`MyControl.cs`

&lt;!-- language: csharp --&gt;

public string Name { get; set; }
public object Value { get; set; }
public string Type { get; set; }

Each control could be different, i.e. if the type is `DateTime` show a `DatePicker`, if it's `Text` show an `Entry` control etc.

For example:

&lt;!-- language: lang-json --&gt;

[
{
"name": "Title",
"value": "Blah",
"type": "string"
},
{
"name": "StartDate",
"value": "12/1/18",
"type": "datetime"
}
]

The JSON could be different for every page.

`ViewModel.cs`

This contains a `ObservableCollection` of the controls.

The `Form.xaml` has

&lt;!-- language: xml --&gt;

&lt;StackLayout x:Name="Properties"&gt;
&lt;/StackLayout&gt;

The `Form.xaml.cs`

&lt;!-- language: csharp --&gt;

foreach (MyControl control in controls)
{
if (control.type == "string")
{
var entry = new Entry();
entry.StyleId = detail.Name;
entry.Placeholder = detail.Name;
entry.Text = detail.Value?.ToString();

entry.BindingContext = control;
//entry.SetBinding(Entry.TextProperty, "#");
//entry.BindingContext = new { Name = control };

Properties.Children.Add(entry);
}
//etc
}

I have a button on my form to submit the data and collect user entry but the binding isn't working.

---

&lt;!-- language: csharp --&gt;

Control.SetBinding(MyControl.SomeBindableProperty, new Binding(nameof(Property), source: sourceObject));

Should it be

&lt;!-- language: csharp --&gt;

entry.SetBinding(Entry.TextProperty, "FormDetails.Value");

